710216f-a.title: Manhattan: 8th Avenue - 52nd Street (West)
710216f-a.text:
Eighth Avenue, east side, north from W. 52nd Street. The
6th Avenue Elevated Line and its 8th Avenue station are on 53rd
Street. Buildings to the right are shortly to come down. Con-
struction of the Municipal Subway uuuder the Avenue (note the plank.
ing) necessitated the sinking of a work shaft and a storare yard.
Two bildings at 53rd Street will remafn. This will open to view
interior structures that run through the block and which are the
skating rlnk and the Guild Theatre.

View 2: February 19, 1933
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS

710217f-a.title: Manhattan: 8th Avenue - 52nd Street (West)
710217f-a.text:
Eighth Avenue, east side, north from W. 52nd Street. Demolition
at the right was for the purpose of sinking a shaft for subway con-
struction under the Avenue. This will remain vacant for years, though
used as a parking lot. On 53rd Street appears the 6th Avenue Elevated
Line a d its 8th Avenue station. 1939 will see the removal of this
obsolete system. At the extreme left is the Columbus Monument at
Columbus Circle. This terminates this thoroughfare. Central Park is
beyond that point.
Views 2 and 3 are limted to the 52nd and 53rd Street frontage.
The Guild Theatre and the Iceland Skating Rink are east of the Avenue
and extend through this block.
View 1: October 20, 1928
View 2: February 19, 1933
View 3: March 30, 1936
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS
